</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A62436ED1046FF97D99EF8BFEA62EB55" blockId="31.[151,1269,1858,1881]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1436,151,618]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1046FFA9D99EF8BFEA09EE66" authority="Holly, 1929: 119" authorityName="Holly" authorityPageNumber="119" authorityYear="1929" box="[151,564,1858,1881]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multispinis">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1046FFA9D99EF8BFE94AEE66" box="[151,375,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ancistrus multispinis</emphasis>
Holly, 1929: 119
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality: Mercado Bléin (
<collectingCountry id="DE8C767D1046FFA9DA8CF8BFEBD6EE66" box="[901,1003,1858,1881]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
). 
<typeStatus id="7920884F1046FFA9DAF4F8BFEC59EE66" box="[1021,1124,1858,1881]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Holotype</typeStatus>
: NMW 8952. 
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D99EFF6AE91AE98E" bold="true" box="[151,295,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Comments:</emphasis>
The type of 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97D8C8FF65EA85E98E" authorityName="Holly" authorityYear="1929" box="[449,696,152,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multispinis">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D8C8FF65EA85E98E" box="[449,696,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ancistrus multispinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been lost for a long time until Mark Sabaj rediscovered it in 2007. The species had been considered a 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DBA2FF3DEB74E9E6" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1904" box="[683,841,192,217]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Lasiancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DBA2FF3DEB74E9E6" box="[683,841,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lasiancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since 
<bibRefCitation id="C20A4B1C1078FF97DA9FFF3DEC62E9E5" author="Isbrucker, I. J. H." box="[918,1119,192,218]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 181" refId="ref29930" refString="Isbrucker, I. J. H. (1980) Classification and catalogue of the mailed Loricariidae (Pisces, Siluriformes). Verslagen en Technische Gegevens, Universiteit van Amsterdam, 22, 1 - 181." type="journal article" year="1980">Isbrücker (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. Armbruster (2005) recognized that the original description was not entirely consistent with a 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DAB0FF15EC6AE83E" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1904" box="[953,1111,232,257]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Lasiancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DAB0FF15EC6AE83E" box="[953,1111,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lasiancistrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but placed the species into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97D86EFEEDEA1BE816" baseAuthorityName="Armbruster" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[359,550,272,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Lasiancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schomburgkii">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D86EFEEDEA1BE816" box="[359,550,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">L. schomburgkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
anyway. The label was clearly misread by Holly as it does say ÒMercado BelémÓ (
<figureCitation id="3EA02A681078FF97D801FEC5E962E86D" box="[264,351,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="32.[151,255,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-40@32.[181,1406,194,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 17. Dorsal, lateral, and ventral vies of the holotype of Ancistrus multispinis NMW 8952, 115.2 mm SL. Photographs by M.H. Sabaj and K. Luckenbill." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5125265" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5125265/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). The species is most certainly a species of 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DA6EFEC5EBEBE86E" box="[871,982,312,337]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DA6EFEC5EBEBE86E" box="[871,982,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Peckoltia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but I have only examined photos provided by Mark Sabaj and Kyle Luckenbill. The species is relatively unique in that it has the lower lip consisting of short, multibranched fimbriae; however, some 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DA06FE75EB45E89E" box="[783,888,392,417]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DA06FE75EB45E89E" box="[783,888,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
approach the condition in 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DDBEFE75ED68E89E" authorityName="Holly" authorityYear="1929" box="[1207,1365,392,417]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Ancistrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multispinis">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DDBEFE75ED68E89E" box="[1207,1365,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P. multispinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only color remaining is some faint, irregular banding in the caudal fin that is consistent with most species of 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97D99EFE25E93BE8CE" box="[151,262,472,497]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D99EFE25E93BE8CE" box="[151,262,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Peckoltia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97D880FE25E9CDE8CE" box="[393,496,472,497]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D880FE25E9CDE8CE" box="[393,496,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P.vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known from around Belém. The species may be valid or a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97D99EFDFDE93DEB26" box="[151,256,512,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97D99EFDFDE93DEB26" box="[151,256,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">P. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I tentatively recognize it as valid, but with the color gone from the type specimen and little pertinent information in the original description, it is impossible to compare the species with other 
<taxonomicName id="619B4D6E1078FF97DDD7FDD5ED70EB7E" box="[1246,1357,552,577]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94EFEAFF1078FF97DDD7FDD5ED70EB7E" box="[1246,1357,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Peckoltia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it is not included in diagnoses or the key.
</paragraph>
